subSubSection.paragraph:
A light brown sinistral shell composed of 11 flat whorls with tubercled spiral ribs. Deep suture. Siphonal canal very short, barely bent. Lip simple, expanded. Length 2.5 linien (
"lines"
), diameter 0.75 linie (L. Pfeiffer probably used the "Preussische Mass" widely used after 1816 until introduction of the metric system; a linie is equivalent to 2.179 mm).
